    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a 3-level hierarchical structure with geographic regions (categorical nominal) as primary nodes, transportation modes (categorical ordinal) as secondary nodes, and vehicle types (categorical nominal) as tertiary nodes. Synthetic values were generated using a base normal distribution (\u03bc=1200, \u03c3=450) with \u00b115% seasonal variation to simulate quarterly fluctuations. Regional totals maintain proportional relationships observed in EU road safety reports while introducing distinct vehicle-type clusters. The sunburst visualization was selected to emphasize part-to-whole relationships through angular encoding, adhering to Tufte's data-ink principles by eliminating redundant gridlines while maintaining Cairo's effectiveness in hierarchical perception through radial color gradients. Color saturation variations (\u0394L* = 20) enhance categorical discrimination while preserving luminosity contrast requirements for accessibility."
